      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the QoI in both validation and COU, providing direct correspondence. However the aggregation method (volume-averaged vs. outlet-flux-weighted) differs between validation dataset and COU prediction, introducing a partial relevance gap. Achieved level 3."
