      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided for selection of hemolysis power-law model over competing models (e.g., strain-based, Lagrangian exposure); sensitivity to model form documented.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was adopted without documented comparison to alternative model forms. No sensitivity analysis on model form uncertainty was performed. This represents a critical gap at MRL 5 where absolute predictions are required. Achieved level 1."
